  "snippet": "His achievements are considered to be on par with those of Albert Einstein, Sir Isaac Newton, and Charles Darwin.( [...] Shannon is credited with the invention of signal-flow graphs, in 1942. He discovered the topological gain formula while investigating the functional operation of an analog computer.( [...] with a PhD in mathematics;( his thesis focusing on genetics contained important results, while initially going unpublished.("
